\label{conj:refined-sharp-kahane}
Let $L(s) = \sum a_n n^{-s}$ be an ordinary Dirichlet series with
entire continuation of order $\le 1$. Then for all $\sigma$ with
$\mu(\sigma) \ge 1$,
\begin{equation}\label{eq:refined-sharp}
  \mu\bigl(\sigma + \mu(\sigma)\bigr) \;=\; 0.
\end{equation}
Equivalently: on any interval where $\mu \ge 1$, the slope of $\mu$
is $\le -1$.

